eipt has been sent\n          to your email address.\n        </AlertDescription>\n      </Alert>\n      <Alert>\n        <InfoIcon />\n        <AlertTitle>New feature available</AlertTitle>\n        <AlertDescription>\n          We&apos;ve added dark mode support. You can enable it in your\n          account settings.\n        </AlertDescription>\n      </Alert>\n    </div>\n  ),\n};\n\n/**\n * Use for the minimal case: a single alert with an icon, title, and\n * description, using the default `variant`.\n *\n * Verbatim from [shadcn Alert ŌĆ║ Basic](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/radix/alert#basic).\n *\n * @summary for a single default-variant alert\n */\nexport const SingleAlert: Story = {\n  args: {\n    children: (\n      <>\n        <CheckCircle2Icon />\n        <AlertTitle>Account updated successfully</AlertTitle>\n        <AlertDescription>\n          Your profile information has been saved. Changes will be reflected\n          immediately.\n        </AlertDescription>\n      </>\n    ),\n  },\n};\n\n/**\n * Use `variant=\"destructive\"` to signal a failed or dangerous outcome (e.g. a\n * failed payment) ŌĆö it tints the icon, title, and description with the\n * destructive color instead of the default card foreground.\n *\n * Verbatim from [shadcn Alert ŌĆ║ Destructive](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/radix/alert#destructive).\n *\n * @summary for destructive/error states\n */\nexport const Destructive: Story = {\n  args: {\n    variant: \"destructive\",\n    children: (\n      <>\n        <AlertCircleIcon />\n        <AlertTitle>Payment failed</AlertTitle>\n        <AlertDescription>\n          Your payment could not be processed. Please check your payment\n          method and try again.\n        </AlertDescription>\n      </>\n    ),\n  },\n};\n\n/**\n * Custom colors are applied directly via `className` (e.g.\n * `border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 text-amber-900` with dark-mode counterparts)\n * since `variant` only covers `default`/`destructive` ŌĆö use this for a\n * warning tone the built-in variants don't provide.\n *\n * Verbatim from [shadcn Alert ŌĆ║ Custom Colors](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/radix/alert#custom-colors).\n *\n * @summary for a custom warning tone via className\n */\nexport const Colors: Story = {\n  args: {\n    className:\n      \"border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 text-amber-900 dark:border-amber-900 dark:bg-amber-950 dark:text-amber-50\",\n    children: (\n      <>\n        <AlertTriangleIcon />\n        <AlertTitle>Your subscription will expire in 3 days.</AlertTitle>\n        <AlertDescription>\n          Renew now to avoid service interruption or upgrade to a paid plan to\n          continue using the service.\n        </AlertDescription>\n      </>\n    ),\n  },\n};\n",
